<item>
            <title>[METAMODEL-152] DataContext.refreshSchemas() not respected by QueryPostprocessDataContext</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/METAMODEL-152</link>
                <project id="12314523" key="METAMODEL">Apache MetaModel (Retired)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve just realized that we have a (probably quite old) critical bug in the sense of QueryPostprocessDataContext doing dirty caching of the main schema. The refreshSchemas() method on the DataContext interface is there to clear any cached schemas but it seems that the main schema is always going to be reused in QueryPostprocessDataContext - a kinda big breach of contract and it impacts a lot of implementations since this class is superclass of many DataContext implementations.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12837713">METAMODEL-152</key>
            <summary>DataContext.refreshSchemas() not respected by QueryPostprocessDataContext</summary>
