                            <comment id="14590525" author="githubbot" created="Wed, 17 Jun 2015 20:31:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;GitHub user kaspersorensen opened a pull request:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/metamodel/pull/30&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/metamodel/pull/30&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/METAMODEL-152&quot; title=&quot;DataContext.refreshSchemas() not respected by QueryPostprocessDataContext&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;METAMODEL-152&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;METAMODEL-152&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    This fixes the pretty critical caching issue we have where even a ```refreshSchemas()``` call does not clear the cache of the &quot;main schema&quot; in QueryPostprocessDataContext.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    I simplified the QueryPostprocessDataContext a bit by not having any cache at all. That&apos;s because there already is a schema cache in it&apos;s superclass, AbstractDataContext.&lt;/p&gt;

